Pre-Game Insights: Estonia clinched the 2024 Baltic Cup crown in June, defeating Lithuania on penalties in the final.
Jurgen Henn’s side beat Lithuania 4-3 on penalties following a 1-1 stalemate with Nacionalinė komanda in normal time.
Estonia secured promotion from League D in 2022 after winning four consecutive matches in the UEFA Nations League.
Slovakia suffered a round-of-16 exit from the 2024 European Championship, losing 2-1 to England in extra time.
Calzona’s men finished as one of the best third-placed teams in Group E, earning four points from a possible nine.
Miscellaneous Highlights: This will be the third-ever meeting between Estonia and Slovakia.
Estonia are on a run of four straight wins in the UEFA Nations League, scoring 10 goals and conceding twice since March 2022.
Slovakia have won just one of their last five Nations League games while losing three and drawing once since June 2022.
